Rule: Application should have used APIKit to auto-generate the implementation interface
Application should have an APIKit Global exception strategy
Configuration files should not have so many flows
Configuration files should not have so many subflows
Flows names should match a naming convention
SubFlows names should match a naming convention
Encryption key should not be logged
Credentials and resources should be managed with application properties
Mule Credentials Vault should not use a hardcoded encryption key
AutoDiscovery should be used to register the app in API manager
HTTP Status codes should have been properly set inside the exception handler
Data Transformations should be stored in external DWL Files - Payload
Data Transformations should be stored in external DWL Files - Variable
HTTP Listener should use HTTPS protocol
HTTP Listener should use a specific port property
API ID in AutoDiscovery should not use a hardcoded value
DB Host name should not use a hardcoded value
Domain - HTTP Requestor reconnection strategy should use a configurable count value
Domain - HTTP Requestor reconnection strategy should use configurable frequency
Domain - Mule Secure Properties should use AES-CBC algorithm
Domain - HTTP Listener should not use a hardcoded port value
Domain - HTTP Requestor should reference a TLS Configuration
Domain - Trust Store Configuration should use a configurable path
Domain - Key Store Configuration should use a configurable path
Domain - Trust Store Configuration should not have the insecure attribute
Domain - HTTPS Listener should have a TLS Configuration
Domain - HTTP Requestor Configuration should not use dynamic default headers or query params
Domain - HTTP Requestor Configuration should have a configurable Response Timeout
